data.title: Review: Big Brovaz, JJB/Puma Arena
data.meta_description: Big Brovaz took over the show for an hour in a hot and sweaty JJB/Puma tent.
data.text:
The group came to prominence last year with their debut single "Nu Flow", taken from the album of the same name and this song proved popular with the V crowds.

Recent hit "Favourite Things" also went down well.

Several women could be seen almost fainting at the front of the stage as band members J-Rock and Randy removed their shirts in the sweltering temperatures.

And, for anyone who didn't know, they reminded us that their new single is coming out on September 1.

Published Sunday August 17, 2003
